Great romantic Georgetown date spot hidden from the bustling M Street. (in Cady’s Alley…walk down the staircase from M Street) Very diverse European menu with a large drink selection. Had a great experience in this spot with my kid. The food came rapidly and the service is just fantastic. Prices are convenient.

The staff at Kafe Leopold’s is like family to me. When I know I’m going for an evening at Kafe Leopold’s, I am sure to be welcomed not as a guest but as a member of their family. It is as if I am walking into a gathering at someone’s home, the service is impeccable and the crowd is bubbly and warm. The outside patio is the perfect place to enjoy an espresso, a drink, and a slice of cake while mingling with others and relaxing to the sound of the water fountain flowing. What makes Kafe Leopold’s unique is not only their A1 quality food and drinks, but the atmosphere that is created through the open and clean decor, elegant indoor outdoor flow, and the most hospitable staff who goes the extra mile to make sure to attend to your every need. A visit to Kafe Leopold's is a must for anyone in the DC area.

No fewer than 7 people came to our table—and at least three of those seemed to be managers of some sort who were just checking in.  Many of the other visits were also totally unnecessary.  Other restaurants are doing a MUCH better job of minimizing the number of contacts between customers and staff.  This one should too!

There were 8 of us and all was well until my daughter discovered a dead bug in her food. We called the waitress and she took the plate away. The manager never came out until i complained about not having the contaminated meal removed from the check. The manager came out and said that the bug was not from the kitchen and it must have landed in the plate from the outdoor patio we were sitting at. He offered no explanation on why he was so sure of his opinion and offered no apology for any inconvenience. He then rudely turned away and left. The check was returned to the table with the charge for the contaminated plate still included. We were very surprised by the treatment and had to argue again to have the charge removed. The Leopold schnitzel was way overrated the meat was not properly tenderized and the bread crumbs did not adhere to the veal. I used to like this place and came here many times. While a bug in the food is not normal its also not the end of the world but in such a situation a restaurant manager should show a customer that they care. The cost of the dish on the bill was not the issue but the fact that the manager was unapologetic and took no responsibility is an indication that there is no accountability in this establishment which makes me wonder what else can one find in a Leopold dish?

Kafe Leopold presents as an upscale cafe; as you walk in to the main dining room, you're greeted with a case of delightful pastries and cakes. The romance ended there for me. I was there for breakfast/brunch and ordered the Italian breakfast. The description was of a dish that contains "crispy polenta" although the soft, flavorless, gelatinous mass under my overcooked eggs and cold mushrooms in no way resembled polenta or anything crispy. I ordered a piece of sacher torte as well, and was saddened on behalf of the city of Vienna at a confection somehow both dry and rubbery. Our server consistently messed up our orders, but was at least polite about it. For what it's worth, my dining companion enjoyed her quiche very much. Hence the second star.
Love this place! A gem in Georgetown!  A lovely afternoon cafe mitt shlag, a quiet spot in the city!

A beautiful European bistro serving a delicious selection of foods and drinks. Hidden in a cute, upscale alley in Georgetown, this restaurant is definitely one of the top ones in DC. I personally love their kale salad 🥗, the flavor is quite refreshing and it's a must every time I visit. The potato soup (seasonal) is also quite tasty and the Käsespätzle (spinach dumplings) is great for all you vegetarians out there. Overall, a wonderful dining experience and highly recommended.

Last Sunday my wife and I had lunch at Cafe Leopold in DC. This is a a nice contemporary Austrian/German "konditorei" ( cakeshop) but by no means only serves delicious cakes and pastries. The modern design is emphasized by great windows with a terrace in front The lunch menu is very elaborate with all the great Austrian/German favourites on it. Presentation is great and portions are not too big. The service was very efficient , prompt and friendly. We loved what we had and topped it off with some great desserts! The brunch menu itself is not too exciting but you can order a la carte from the regular menu like we did. Highly Recommended!

Georgetown gem!

I like this place but a recent visit ended weirdly.  We had a great dinner and asked for coffee.  The coffee never came, so when we asked for the check, of course we didn't expect the coffee to be on it. That was not the case, and our waiter, Juan, was unable to locate Sebastian, the manager, to void the check. The hostess wasn't able to find Sebastian, either so we just paid the incorrect check, and I left a not on the check asking to be contacted about the issue. I never heard from the restaurant, so a couple of days later I called the restaurant and spoke to Sebastian, who said that he was, indeed, in the restaurant on the night we dined, and wondered why we were told otherwise. He apologized, and offered to do something for us during a forthcoming visit, but we declined. The food is great, but unfortunately the place doesn't seem to be very well-run these days.
